TY  - JOUR
AU  - Inderst, Roman
AU  - Pfeil, Sebastian
T1  - Securitization and Compensation in Financial Institutions*
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfs032
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 17
IS  - 4
SP  - 1323
EP  - 1364
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We analyze the interaction between financial institutions’ internal compensation policy, the quality of loans, and their securitization decision. We show when mandatory deferred bonus pay makes incentives more commensurate with the longer term risk of their transactions and hence improves the quality of loans. We also show when it has the opposite effect. We further analyze when mandatory deferred compensation can complement a policy that requires financial institutions to retain a minimum exposure to their originated loans, and we discuss the impact of a tax on short-term bonus pay. Generally, our framework allows us to study the interaction of financial institutions’ internal agency problems with the external agency problem that arises from securitization.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfs032
ER  - 



